==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yen
<hw>Yen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The unit of value and
account in Japan. The <ex>yen</ex> is equal to 100 <xex>sen</xex>. From
Japan's adoption of the gold standard, in 1897, to about 1913 the value
of the yen was about 50 cents. In 1997 and 1998 the value of the yen
varied from 80 per U. S. dollar to 120 per dollar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yend</ent>⟦br⟧
